{{Infobox Artwork | image_file=Le_Reve_Transforme.jpg | backcolor=#FBF5DF | painting_alignment=right | image_size=300px | title=Le Rêve Transformé | artist=[[Giorgio de Chirico]] | year=1913 | medium=[[Oil painting|Oil on canvas]] | height_metric=63 | width_metric=125 | height_imperial=25 | width_imperial= 49 | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | city=[[St. Louis, Missouri]] | museum=[[Saint Louis Art Museum]] }} '''''Le Rêve Transformé''''' (in English, ''The Transformed Dream'') is a 1913 painting by the [[Italy|Italian]] [[Metaphysical art|metaphysical painter]] [[Giorgio De Chirico]]. This work contains the classic De Chirico's images of an empty urban scene at late evening with a ghostly train on the horizon. In this case in the foreground is an arrangement of bananas, pineapples and a Greek sculpture.
{{Giorgio de Chirico}}
